.TH wxTreeCtrl 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxTreeCtrl \- A tree control presents information as a hierarchy, with items that may be expanded to show further items.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Items in a tree control are referenced by \fIwxTreeItemId\fR (not implemented in wx) handles, which may be tested for validity by calling \fIwxTreeItemId::IsOk()\fR (not implemented in wx).

.PP
A similar control with a fully native implementation for GTK+ and macOS as well is \fIwxDataViewTreeCtrl\fR (not implemented in wx).

.PP
To intercept events from a tree control, use the event table macros described in \fIwxTreeEvent\fR.

