.RE
.B
\fBgetItemTextColour(This, Item) -> wx:wx_colour4()\fR
\fB                           when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the colour of the item label.


.RE
.B
\fBgetLastChild(This, Item) -> integer()\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the last child of the item (or an invalid tree item if this item has no children).

.PP
See:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIgetFirstChild/2\fR

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIgetNextSibling/2\fR

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIgetLastChild/2\fR

.RE


.RE
.B
\fBgetNextChild(This, Item, Cookie) -> Result\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          Result ::\fR
\fB                              {Res :: integer(), Cookie :: integer()},\fR
\fB                          This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                          Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                          Cookie :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the next child; call \fIgetFirstChild/2\fR for the first child.

.PP
For this enumeration function you must pass in a 'cookie' parameter which is opaque for the application but is necessary for the library to make these functions reentrant (i.e. allow more than one enumeration on one and the same object simultaneously). The cookie passed to \fIgetFirstChild/2\fR and \fIgetNextChild/3\fR should be the same.

.PP
Returns an invalid tree item if there are no further children.

.PP
See: \fIgetFirstChild/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBgetNextSibling(This, Item) -> integer()\fR
\fB                        when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the next sibling of the specified item; call \fIgetPrevSibling/2\fR for the previous sibling.

.PP
Returns an invalid tree item if there are no further siblings.

.PP
See: \fIgetPrevSibling/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBgetNextVisible(This, Item) -> integer()\fR
\fB                        when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the next visible item or an invalid item if this item is the last visible one.

.PP
Note: The \fIitem\fR itself must be visible.


.RE
.B
\fBgetPrevSibling(This, Item) -> integer()\fR
\fB                        when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the previous sibling of the specified item; call \fIgetNextSibling/2\fR for the next sibling.

.PP
Returns an invalid tree item if there are no further children.

.PP
See: \fIgetNextSibling/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBgetPrevVisible(This, Item) -> integer()\fR
\fB                        when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the previous visible item or an invalid item if this item is the first visible one.

.PP
Note: The \fIitem\fR itself must be visible.


.RE
.B
\fBgetRootItem(This) -> integer() when This :: wxTreeCtrl().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the root item for the tree control.


.RE
.B
\fBgetSelection(This) -> integer() when This :: wxTreeCtrl().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the selection, or an invalid item if there is no selection.

.PP
This function only works with the controls without \fIwxTR_MULTIPLE\fR style, use \fIgetSelections/1\fR for the controls which do have this style or, if a single item is wanted, use \fIGetFocusedItem()\fR (not implemented in wx).


.RE
.B
\fBgetSelections(This) -> Result\fR
\fB                       when\fR
\fB                           Result ::\fR
\fB                               {Res :: integer(),\fR
\fB                                Selection :: [integer()]},\fR
\fB                           This :: wxTreeCtrl().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Fills the array of tree items passed in with the currently selected items.

.PP
This function can be called only if the control has the \fIwxTR_MULTIPLE\fR style.

.PP
Returns the number of selected items.


.RE
.B
\fBgetStateImageList(This) -> wxImageList:wxImageList()\fR
\fB                           when This :: wxTreeCtrl().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the state image list (from which application-defined state images are taken).


.RE
.B
\fBhitTest(This, Point) -> Result\fR
\fB                 when\fR
\fB                     Result :: {Res :: integer(), Flags :: integer()},\fR
\fB                     This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                     Point :: {X :: integer(), Y :: integer()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Calculates which (if any) item is under the given \fIpoint\fR, returning the tree item id at this point plus extra information \fIflags\fR.

.PP
\fIflags\fR is a bitlist of the following:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_ABOVE:\fR Above the client area.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_BELOW:\fR Below the client area.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_NOWHERE:\fR In the client area but below the last item.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_ONITEMBUTTON:\fR On the button associated with an item.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_ONITEMICON:\fR On the bitmap associated with an item.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_ONITEMINDENT:\fR In the indentation associated with an item.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_ONITEMLABEL:\fR On the label (string) associated with an item.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_ONITEMRIGHT:\fR In the area to the right of an item.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_ONITEMSTATEICON:\fR On the state icon for a tree view item that is in a user-defined state.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_TOLEFT:\fR To the right of the client area.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxTREE_HITTEST_TORIGHT:\fR To the left of the client area.

.RE


.RE
.B
\fBinsertItem(This, Parent, Previous, Text, [Option]) -> integer()\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                        Parent :: integer(),\fR
\fB                        Previous :: integer(),\fR
\fB                        Text :: unicode:chardata(),\fR
\fB                        Option ::\fR
\fB                            {image, integer()} |\fR
\fB                            {selImage, integer()} |\fR
\fB                            {data, term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Inserts an item after a given one (\fIprevious\fR).

.PP
The \fIimage\fR and \fIselImage\fR parameters are an index within the normal image list specifying the image to use for unselected and selected items, respectively. If \fIimage\fR > -1 and \fIselImage\fR is -1, the same image is used for both selected and unselected items.


.RE
.B
\fBisBold(This, Item) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the given item is in bold state.

.PP
See: \fIsetItemBold/3\fR


.RE
.B
\fBisExpanded(This, Item) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                    when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the item is expanded (only makes sense if it has children).


.RE
.B
\fBisSelected(This, Item) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                    when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the item is selected.


.RE
.B
\fBisTreeItemIdOk(Item) -> boolean() when Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the item is valid.


.RE
.B
\fBisVisible(This, Item) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                   when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the item is visible on the screen.


.RE
.B
\fBitemHasChildren(This, Item) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                         when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the item has children.


.RE
.B
\fBnew() -> wxTreeCtrl().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Default Constructor.


.RE
.B
\fBnew(Parent, [Option]) -> wxTreeCtrl()\fR
\fB             when\fR
\fB                 Parent :: wxWindow:wxWindow(),\fR
\fB                 Option ::\fR
\fB                     {id, integer()} |\fR
\fB                     {pos, {X :: integer(), Y :: integer()}} |\fR
\fB                     {size, {W :: integer(), H :: integer()}} |\fR
\fB                     {style, integer()} |\fR
\fB                     {validator, wx:wx_object()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Constructor, creating and showing a tree control.

.PP
See: \fIcreate/3\fR


.RE
.B
\fBprependItem(This, Parent, Text, [Option]) -> integer()\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                         Parent :: integer(),\fR
\fB                         Text :: unicode:chardata(),\fR
\fB                         Option ::\fR
\fB                             {image, integer()} |\fR
\fB                             {selectedImage, integer()} |\fR
\fB                             {data, term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Appends an item as the first child of \fIparent\fR, return a new item id.

.PP
The \fIimage\fR and \fIselImage\fR parameters are an index within the normal image list specifying the image to use for unselected and selected items, respectively. If \fIimage\fR > -1 and \fIselImage\fR is -1, the same image is used for both selected and unselected items.


.RE
.B
\fBscrollTo(This, Item) -> ok\fR
\fB                  when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Scrolls the specified item into view.

.PP
Note that this method doesn't work while the window is frozen (See \fIwxWindow:freeze/1\fR), at least under MSW.

.PP
See: \fIensureVisible/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBselectItem(This, Item, [Option]) -> ok\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                        Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                        Option :: {select, boolean()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Selects the given item.

.PP
In multiple selection controls, can be also used to deselect a currently selected item if the value of \fIselect\fR is false.

.PP
Notice that calling this method will generate \fIwxEVT_TREE_SEL_CHANGING\fR and \fIwxEVT_TREE_SEL_CHANGED\fR events and that the change could be vetoed by the former event handler.


.RE
.B
\fBsetImageList(This, ImageList) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                          ImageList :: wxImageList:wxImageList().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the normal image list.

.PP
The image list assigned with this method will \fInot\fR be deleted by \fIwxTreeCtrl\fR's destructor, you must delete it yourself.

.PP
See: \fIassignImageList/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBsetIndent(This, Indent) -> ok\fR
\fB                   when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Indent :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the indentation for the tree control.


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemBackgroundColour(This, Item, Col) -> ok\fR
\fB                                 when\fR
\fB                                     This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                                     Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                                     Col :: wx:wx_colour().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the colour of the item's background.


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemBold(This, Item, [Option]) -> ok\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                         Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                         Option :: {bold, boolean()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Makes item appear in bold font if \fIbold\fR parameter is true or resets it to the normal state.

.PP
See: \fIisBold/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemData(This, Item, Data) -> ok\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                         Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                         Data :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the item client data.

.PP
Notice that the client data previously associated with the \fIitem\fR (if any) is \fInot\fR freed by this function and so calling this function multiple times for the same item will result in memory leaks unless you delete the old item data pointer yourself.


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemDropHighlight(This, Item, [Option]) -> ok\fR
\fB                              when\fR
\fB                                  This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                                  Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                                  Option :: {highlight, boolean()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Gives the item the visual feedback for Drag'n'Drop actions, which is useful if something is dragged from the outside onto the tree control (as opposed to a DnD operation within the tree control, which already is implemented internally).


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemFont(This, Item, Font) -> ok\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                         Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                         Font :: wxFont:wxFont().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the item's font.

.PP
All items in the tree should have the same height to avoid text clipping, so the fonts height should be the same for all of them, although font attributes may vary.

.PP
See: \fIsetItemBold/3\fR


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemHasChildren(This, Item, [Option]) -> ok\fR
\fB                            when\fR
\fB                                This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                                Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                                Option :: {has, boolean()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Force appearance of the button next to the item.

.PP
This is useful to allow the user to expand the items which don't have any children now, but instead adding them only when needed, thus minimizing memory usage and loading time.


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemImage(This, Item, Image, [Option]) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                          Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                          Image :: integer(),\fR
\fB                          Option :: {which, wx:wx_enum()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the specified item's image.

.PP
See \fIgetItemImage/3\fR for the description of the \fIwhich\fR parameter.


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemText(This, Item, Text) -> ok\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                         Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                         Text :: unicode:chardata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the item label.


.RE
.B
\fBsetItemTextColour(This, Item, Col) -> ok\fR
\fB                           when\fR
\fB                               This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                               Item :: integer(),\fR
\fB                               Col :: wx:wx_colour().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the colour of the item's text.


.RE
.B
\fBsetStateImageList(This, ImageList) -> ok\fR
\fB                           when\fR
\fB                               This :: wxTreeCtrl(),\fR
\fB                               ImageList :: wxImageList:wxImageList().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the state image list (from which application-defined state images are taken).

.PP
Image list assigned with this method will \fInot\fR be deleted by \fIwxTreeCtrl\fR's destructor, you must delete it yourself.

.PP
See: \fIassignStateImageList/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBsetWindowStyle(This, Styles) -> ok\fR
\fB                        when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Styles :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the mode flags associated with the display of the tree control.

.PP
The new mode takes effect immediately.

.PP
Note: Generic only; MSW ignores changes.


.RE
.B
\fBsortChildren(This, Item) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sorts the children of the given item using \fIOnCompareItems()\fR (not implemented in wx).

.PP
You should override that method to change the sort order (the default is ascending case-sensitive alphabetical order).


.RE
.B
\fBtoggle(This, Item) -> ok\fR
\fB                when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Toggles the given item between collapsed and expanded states.


.RE
.B
\fBtoggleItemSelection(This, Item) -> ok\fR
\fB                             when\fR
\fB                                 This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Toggles the given item between selected and unselected states.

.PP
For multiselection controls only.


.RE
.B
\fBunselect(This) -> ok when This :: wxTreeCtrl().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Removes the selection from the currently selected item (if any).


.RE
.B
\fBunselectAll(This) -> ok when This :: wxTreeCtrl().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
This function either behaves the same as \fIunselect/1\fR if the control doesn't have \fIwxTR\\_MULTIPLE\fR style, or removes the selection from all items if it does have this style.


.RE
.B
\fBunselectItem(This, Item) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxTreeCtrl(), Item :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Unselects the given item.

.PP
This works in multiselection controls only.


.RE
